Class RegistrationPageController

  • java.lang.Object
    • screensframework.RegistrationPageController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.fxml.Initializable, ControlledScreen

    public class RegistrationPageController
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable, ControlledScreen
    FXML Controller for the Registration page. Allows a User to register as a new Customer, then sends them to the Customer homepage.
    Author:
    Mark Backhouse

      • generateCustID

        private java.lang.String generateCustID(int number)
        Generates a new Customer ID for the Customer.
        Parameters:
        number - Length of the customer database, as an integer.
        Returns:
        A 3-digit String representation of the customer's unique ID. e.g. if they are the 5th customer, their ID will be "005". If they are the 99th customer, their ID will be "099". Limits the system to 1000 customers.

      • register

        private void register(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
               throws java.io.IOException
        Checks the Registration conditions. If all these are met, creates a new Customer object and sends the Customer to the homepage.
        Parameters:
        event - "Register" button clicked.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - the database file could not be found.
